<p>The <code>while</code> tag loops while a condition is true.</p>

<h2>Basic While Loop</h2>
<pre>{open}set $i = 1{close}
{open}while $i le 5{close}
  Item {open}$i{close}
  {open}increment $i{close}
{open}/while{close}</pre>
{set $i = 1}
<ul>
{while $i le 5}
  <li>Item {$i}</li>
  {increment $i}
{/while}
</ul>

<h2>While with Decrement</h2>
<pre>{open}set $countdown = 5{close}
{open}while $countdown gt 0{close}
  {open}$countdown{close}...
  {open}decrement $countdown{close}
{open}/while{close}
Liftoff!</pre>
{set $countdown = 5}
<p>
{while $countdown gt 0}
{$countdown}...
{decrement $countdown}
{/while}
Liftoff!</p>

<h2>Nested While Loops</h2>
<pre>{open}set $row = 1{close}
{open}while $row le 3{close}
  {open}set $col = 1{close}
  {open}while $col le 4{close}
    ({open}$row{close},{open}$col{close})
    {open}increment $col{close}
  {open}/while{close}
  {open}increment $row{close}
{open}/while{close}</pre>
<table border="1">
{set $row = 1}
{while $row le 3}
  <tr>
  {set $col = 1}
  {while $col le 4}
    <td>({$row},{$col})</td>
    {increment $col}
  {/while}
  </tr>
  {increment $row}
{/while}
</table>
